OL,5, MPs are earning up to #350 an hour to  
OL,6, take surveys for polling companies,    
OL,7, according to BBC research.             
OL,9,FFirms such as YouGov and Ipsos Mori    
OL,10,Fregularly question MPs on behalf of    
OL,11,Fbusinesses and charities to find out   
OL,12,Fthe opinions of policy makers.         
OL,14,FSince the 2019 election, 123 MPs have  
OL,15,Fspent 695 hours carrying out 1,040     
OL,16,Fsurveys - earning more than #116,000.  
OL,18,FThey are not breaking conduct rules if 
OL,19,Fthe earnings are declared, but it comes
OL,20,Famid renewed scrutiny of outside work. 
